{{BLP primary sources|date=May 2018}}
'''Barbara Goff''' is a Classics Professor at [[The University of Reading]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Staff Profile:Professor Barbara Goff|url=https://www.reading.ac.uk/classics/about/staff/b-e-goff.aspx|publisher=University of Reading|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> She is well known for her contribution to the classics world in relation to her interests in [[Greek tragedy|Greek Tragedy]] and its [[Classical reception studies|reception]]; women in antiquity; [[Postcolonialism|postcolonial]] classics and reception of Greek political thought.

== Education ==
Goff is a [[King's College, Cambridge|King's College Cambridge]] Alumni, where she did her undergraduate degree. She later completed her Postgraduate work at [[University of California|The University of California]].

== Career ==
After her first job as a [[Junior Research Fellow]] at Kings College Cambridge, Goff has worked in different institutions all over the world including [[University of Texas at Austin|The University of Texas at Austin.]]

Goff is currently lecturing at the University of Reading, leading modules focusing on ancient drama, ancient Greek language, ancient sport, and sexuality and gender in the ancient world.

== Research Groups and Centres ==
As a lecturer at The University of Reading Goff is a member of the Ancient Literature and Classical Tradition and Reception groups in the Department.

Including this, Goff is a member of the Ancient and Modern Imperialisms Network, based in Reading and helps to run the Legacy of Greek Political Thought Network, based in Reading, and the Classical Reception Studies Network, based at the [[Open University]].

Goff is on the international editorial boards of  the ''Classical Receptions Journal'' (OUP) and of ''Elektra'' (University of Patras) and is  on the Advisory Board of the AHRC project 'Classics and Class', based in [[King's College London]].

