'''Lynne Duval''' (née '''Robinson''', born 21 June 1969)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iaaf.org/athletes/great-britain-ni/lynne-robinson-61605|work=IAAF |title=Lynne Robinson |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> is an English former [[Middle-distance running|middle-distance]] runner. She finished fourth in the [[800 metres]] final at the [[1986 World Junior Championships in Athletics|1986 World Junior Championships]] and went on to win the [[1500 metres]] title at the [[Athletics at the 1993 Summer Universiade|1993 Universiade]].
==Career== A member of Coventry Godiva Harriers, Robinson was a successful junior who won the AAA Under 17 800 m title in 1984 and 1985,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/bc/waaaj.htm |work=GBR Athletics |title=AAA Junior Championships (women) |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> and finished fourth in the [[800 metres]] final at the [[1986 World Junior Championships in Athletics|1986 World Junior Championships]] in 2:02.18. Her best time for the 800 m was achieved on 26 July 1989 in Wythenshawe, when she ran 2:02.0.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/uk/wb99.htm |work=GBR Athletics |title=UK all-time list (women) |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref>
Robinson won the [[1992 UK Athletics Championships|1992 UK Championships]] 800m title, narrowly defeating Coventry Godiva clubmate, [[Lorraine Baker]], 2:04.47 to 2:04.52,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/bc/uk.htm |work=GBR Athletics |title=UK Championships |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> and went on to finish fourth in the 800 m final at the 1992 [[AAA Championships]]/Olympic trials. The highlight of her career came when she won the [[1500 metres]] title at the [[Athletics at the 1993 Summer Universiade|1993 Universiade]] in [[Buffalo, New York]], in a time of 4:12.03.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/ic/wsgw.htm |work=GBR Athletics |title=World Student Games (Universiade – Women) |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> Her 1500m best of 4:10.32 was set on 30 July 1994 in Hechtel.
Robinson has a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] in Social History from [[Warwick University]] (1997) and is a lecturer at [[Staffordshire University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.staffs.ac.uk/staff/profiles/ld2.jsp |work=Staffordshire University |title= Dr Lynne Duval |accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref>
==International competitions== {| {{AchievementTable|Event=yes}} |- !colspan=6|Representing {{GBR2}} |- |rowspan=2|1985 |rowspan=2|[[1985 European Athletics Junior Championships|European Junior Championships]] |rowspan=2|[[Cottbus]], Germany |15th (sf) |800 m |2:13.35 |- |bgcolor=cc9966|3rd |4 × 400 m |3:35.10 |- |1986 |[[1986 World Junior Championships in Athletics|World Junior Championships]] |[[Athens]], Greece |4th |800 m |2:02.18 |- |1987 |[[1987 European Athletics Junior Championships|European Junior Championships]] |[[Birmingham]], United Kingdom |6th |800 m |2:05.14 |- |1991 |[[Athletics at the 1991 Summer Universiade|Universiade]] |[[Sheffield]], United Kingdom |6th |1500 m |4:13.40 |- |1993 |[[Athletics at the 1993 Summer Universiade|Universiade]] |[[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], United States |bgcolor=gold|1st |1500 m |4:12.03 |- !colspan=6|<small>''' (sf) Indicates overall position in semifinal round'''</small> |}
