{{Infobox deity | type = Greek | name = Theandrios, Theandrites | image = | alt = | caption = | god_of = | abode = | symbol = | consort = | parents = | siblings = | children = | mount = [[Mount Hermon]] | Roman_equivalent = [[Dionysus|Dionysius]] }} {{Fertile Crescent myth (Arabian)}} In [[Ancient Greek religion|Greek religion]] and [[Greek mythology|mythology]], '''Theandrios''' ({{lang-el|Θεάνδριος}}, "God-Man") or '''Theandrates''' (Θεανδράτης) is a [[deity]] that was worshipped in towns and villages around [[Mount Hermon]] by [[Tribes of Arabia|North Arabian tribes]] of [[pre-Islamic Arabia]].<ref name="Moralee2004">{{cite book|author=Jason Moralee|title=For Salvation's Sake: Provincial Loyalty, Personal Religion, and Epigraphic Production in the Roman and Late Antique Near East|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2XZOc0jdD0gC&pg=PA34|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=18 May 2004|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-96778-5|pages=34–}}</ref> Theandrios is evidenced by a dedication to a male god found at [[Beit Rime]], [[Syria]] and it is supposed that the Greek name was imposed on a previous god of the region.<ref name="Kaizer2008">{{cite book|author=Ted Kaizer|title=The Variety of Local Religious Life in the Near East In the Hellenistic and Roman Periods|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KgVD3WL0vAsC&pg=PA87|accessdate=18 September 2012|year=2008|publisher=BRILL|isbn=978-90-04-16735-3|pages=87–}}</ref> He has been considered the [[Arabian]] version of similar "God-man" deities such as [[Dionysus|Dionysius]], [[Herakles]]/[[Hercules]], [[Mithras]], [[Krishna]] and [[Jesus]].<ref name="Robertson2004">{{cite book|author=John M. Robertson|title=A Short History of Christianity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aqDdaLodingC&pg=PA24|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=1 April 2004|publisher=Kessinger Publishing|isbn=978-0-7661-8909-6|pages=24–}}</ref><ref name="WearDillon2007">{{cite book|author1=Sarah Klitenic Wear|author2=John M. Dillon|title=Dionysius the Areopagite and the Neoplatonist Tradition: Despoiling the Hellenes|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fyfG05phUz0C&pg=PA6|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=30 September 2007|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-0-7546-0385-6|pages=6–}}</ref>
